President Biden has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key roles, including the Board of Visitors to the United States Merchant Marine Academy, the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board, and the Library of Congress Trust Fund Board.

For the Board of Visitors to the United States Merchant Marine Academy, President Biden intends to appoint Claudia Cimini, Executive Vice President of the Marine Engineers Beneficial Association; Susan A. Davis, former Congressional Representative from San Diego; Eric P. Ebeling, President and CEO of American Roll-On Roll-Off Carrier Group; Nicholas M. Logothetis, Vice Chairman of Libra Group; and Captain Michael J. Rodriguez, a maritime professional.

Jed Katz, Managing Director of Javelin Venture Partners, will be appointed to the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board.

Eric Mindich, Founder and CEO of Everblue Management, will be appointed to the Library of Congress Trust Fund Board.

Lastly, William Inboden, Professor and Director of the Alexander Hamilton Center at the University of Florida, will be appointed as a Commissioner for the U.S. Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad.

These individuals will provide advice and recommendations on various matters related to their respective roles.